# tooling-gh-tidy-myrmidon-rebase-swarm — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-05-03)

**Changed by:** ProjectMnemosyne /learn — observed hephaestus-tidy swarm crash on ProjectMnemosyne branches
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed

- Added new "When to Use" trigger: `rate_limit_event` crash in agent swarm
- Added new Failed Attempts row: all agents crash with `Unknown message type: rate_limit_event`
- Added workaround (parallel `Agent()` calls) to Verified Workflow
- Added suggested fix (catch `rate_limit_event` in event loop) to Results & Parameters
- Updated `verification` field from `verified-precommit` to `verified-local` (workaround executed end-to-end)
- Bumped version 1.0.0 → 1.1.0

### Why

Running `/hephaestus:tidy` on ProjectMnemosyne revealed that the swarm dispatch loop in
`hephaestus/github/tidy.py` does not handle the `rate_limit_event` message type emitted by
`claude-code-sdk`. All 10 agents failed in ~4 seconds with
`Unknown message type: rate_limit_event`. The root issue is in the SDK event loop, not
actual rate limiting. A workaround using direct parallel `Agent()` calls resolved all 5
real conflicts successfully.

